            <p>The CSS Working Group has a document online of &#8220;&#8230;Mistakes in the Design of CSS&#8221;, one of them is this:</p>
<p>&#8220;Flexbox should have been less crazy about flex-basis vs width/height. Perhaps: if width/height is auto, use flex-basis; otherwise, stick with width/height as an inflexible size. (This also makes min/max width/height behavior fall out of the generic definition.)&#8221;</p>
<p>Can you talk about what they mean by this?</p>

