    <li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-1599014">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1599014">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2c1a222a5b48d83a988fe206640bd4e6?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-01-12T10:14:14+00:00">January 12, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Kazi"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Kazi</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>@Josh McCullough its pretty simple to achieve that, better and easier then ever before. Just use the flex property and set it to 1, for e.g:</p>
<pre><code>.someClass {
   flex: 1;
   color: #ebebeb;
   padding: 2rem;
}
</code></pre>
<p>flex is a very powerful property and can be used in the shorthand of flex: 1 1 auto; (grow, shrink and basis) &#8211; using just flex: 1 tells it to take all the remaining space thus making the footer stick at the bottom. Look an eye out for grid to make a proper entry into the browsers and we would be having magic on our plates in terms of layouts.</p>
<p>See it live in action:<br />
<iframe id="cp_embed_WrOqma" src="https://codepen.io/anon/embed/preview/WrOqma?height=300&amp;slug-hash=WrOqma&amp;default-tab=result&amp;host=http%3A%2F%2Fcodepen.io" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" height="300" allowtransparency="true" class="cp_embed_iframe" style="width: 100%; overflow: hidden;"></iframe></p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
                      </div>
