        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2013-07-10T08:01:37+00:00">July 10, 2013</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="tinabeans"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> tinabeans</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>In your second Codepen example (with the blue navigation bar), I couldn&#8217;t figure out why the flow-direction: column doesn&#8217;t seem to kick in at the smallest screen width. I played around with a few values and found that explicitly adding some height to the ul.navigation made the li&#8217;s stack vertically. Is there a better way around this without requiring a hard-coded height?</p>

