      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-537354">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/227f83b497a8bec9d0549617d0d28a6f?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2013-09-06T02:48:43+00:00">September 6, 2013</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="SelenIT"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> SelenIT</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Firefox 22+ has unprefixed Flexbox, but, unfortunately, it still doesn&#8217;t support flex-wrap property (and hence flex-flow shorthand). So the wonderful example with 3-column layout reducing to 1 column on narrow screen in Firefox looks really messy. But it&#8217;s possible to create its simplified analog that works in both Chromium-based browsers and Firefox 23+: <a href="http://codepen.io/anon/pen/pEIKu" rel="nofollow">http://codepen.io/anon/pen/pEIKu</a></p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-537354' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-537354", "537354", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to SelenIT'>Reply</a>          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      
    
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->

