        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2013-12-12T17:42:12+00:00">December 12, 2013</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="mono"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> mono</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Chris, I couldn&#8217;t vertically align some content in print media, do you know where I could find more information about this kind of support?</p>
<p>My test looks something like this,</p>
<p>CSS:</p>
<pre><code>@page {
    size: US-Letter;
}
article {
    page-break-after: always;
    text-align: center;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}
article:last-child {
    page-break-after: avoid;
}
</code></pre>
<p>HTML:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;article&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;
            Hello
        &lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;/article&gt;

    &lt;article&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;
            Hello 2
        &lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;/article&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
</code></pre>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
