    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-1134249">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1134249">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/53768431bd5f79ac7cc9185d8412e533?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-02-04T06:29:31+00:00">February 4, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Jan"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Jan</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Hy,</p>
<p>in your first example, the child element has been centered by (magic!) margin: auto;</p>
<p>This solution does not work in IE11 if the child element has no defined height, for example, if the height is determined by the content.</p>
<p>All other browsers behave as expected.</p>
<pre><code class="css">.parent {
  display: flex;
  height: 300px; /* Or whatever */
}

.child {
  width: 100px;  /* Or whatever */
  height: 100px; /* Or whatever  ---- Doesn't work in IE11, if the height is determined by the content ---- */
  margin: auto;  /* Magic! */
}
</code></pre>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1134249' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1134249", "1134249", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Jan'>Reply</a>          </div>
