    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-1544695">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1544695">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c59b3876d77c49fae5e615dec5d9c582?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-04-09T01:32:42+00:00">April 9, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Stuart"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Stuart</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>This really annoyed me and was broken for a bit, so I wanted to share in case anyone ever comes across this in the future. If you need to support blackberry 7+, make sure you use</p>
<p><code>-webkit-box-orient: vertical;<br />
    -moz-box-orient: vertical;<br />
    -webkit-box-direction: normal;<br />
    -moz-box-direction: normal;<br />
    -webkit-flex-direction: column;<br />
    -ms-flex-direction: column;<br />
    flex-direction: column;</code></p>
<p>&#8230;if you use row wrap, it doesn&#8217;t wrap and just puts everything side-by-side. Also, very important. Make sure the child elements of the parent flex container don&#8217;t have <code>display: inline;</code> applied to them. It breaks it for some reason. I hope this helps someone!</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1544695' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1544695", "1544695", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Stuart'>Reply</a>          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      
    
  <ul class="children">

    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-1563853">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1563853">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c59b3876d77c49fae5e615dec5d9c582?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-04-12T03:16:05+00:00">April 12, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Stuart"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Stuart</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>One last important thing to remember if you have to support blackberry 7+&#8230;make sure all child elements have <code>float:none</code> applied to them&#8230;if floats are applied, they&#8217;ll just not appear. I hope this helps!</p>

          </div>
