        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-05-04T23:23:59+00:00">May 4, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Guilherme Bruzzi"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Guilherme Bruzzi</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Hi Chris! Very nice article! But the last example &#8220;mobile-first 3-columns layout with full-width header and footer&#8221; in my 34.0.1847.131 chrome didn&#8217;t make the two sidebars half of the size of the main content.<br />
I had to write:<br />
    @media all and (min-width: 800px) {<br />
      .aside-1 { order: 1; flex: 1 25%; }<br />
      .main    { order: 2; flex: 2 1 50%; }<br />
      .aside-2 { order: 3; flex: 1 25%; }<br />
      .footer  { order: 4; }<br />
    }<br />
On the last media query in order to do that ( <a href="http://cdpn.io/rhbmd" title="codepen link" rel="nofollow">http://cdpn.io/rhbmd</a> ).</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
