        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/668ac2ccc43106425cc429e791f2f596?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-06-05T23:36:33+00:00">June 5, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Tilwin joy"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Tilwin joy</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>main axis &#8211; &#8220;The main axis of a flex container is the primary axis along which flex items are laid out. Beware, it is not necessarily horizontal; it depends on the justify-content property (see below).&#8221;</p>
<p>flex-direction &#8211; &#8220;This establishes the main-axis,…&#8221;</p>
<p>These two are in conflict right..? :)</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1582202' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1582202", "1582202", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Tilwin joy'>Reply</a>          </div>
