        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-08-22T01:51:05+00:00">August 22, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Fredrik"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Fredrik</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I&#8217;ve been experimenting with <code>flex-wrap</code> recently, and found that Safari doesn&#8217;t support it (on desktop or mobile), although it claims to, ie. <code>Modernizr.flexwrap</code> is true. I&#8217;ve <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/issues/1414" rel="nofollow">filed a bug report with Modernizr</a> for this. Wanted to spread the word, since there seems to be some confusion around this property flying around in the wake of Firefox previously not having supported it.</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1584625' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1584625", "1584625", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Fredrik'>Reply</a>          </div>
