        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2014-10-21T16:14:02+00:00">October 21, 2014</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="coolcat007"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> coolcat007</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I kind of agree with the article. Both Flexbox and Grid layout have their pro&#8217;s and cons. The flexbox is more suitable for dynamic content (think about displaying a random amount of images of a random size), where the grid layout is preferable for known content areas. Both can adjust for the screensize, but are optimized for different applications.</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1586127' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1586127", "1586127", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to coolcat007'>Reply</a>          </div>
