        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2015-03-20T07:43:21+00:00">March 20, 2015</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Ivan Kleshnin"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Ivan Kleshnin</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Warning! Description of justify-content / align-items is incorrect. Behavior of the last two changes depending of flex-direction. Article says it should be independent. &#8220;This defines the alignment along the main axis.&#8221; No! If flex-direction = column, that will align items along the cross axis. To align items along main axis you&#8217;ll need to change align-items instead.</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1593300' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1593300", "1593300", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Ivan Kleshnin'>Reply</a>          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      
    
  <ul class="children">

    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-chriscoyier bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-1593303">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1593303">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e6e3b0dc1a26476da301047fb70784e5?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2015-03-20T08:06:37+00:00">March 20, 2015</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Chris Coyier"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Chris Coyier</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>When you change the flex direction, you&#8217;re changing the main axis. That&#8217;s how I think about it anyway. Flex-direction:</p>
<blockquote><p>
  establishes the main-axis
</p></blockquote>

          </div>
