    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-launchoverit even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-1593464">

      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1593464">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/90aa2a3a916d063a8f4e65d62324914c?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2015-03-27T11:00:55+00:00">March 27, 2015</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="launchoverit"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> launchoverit</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I’m new to flexbox and certainly don’t want to spread my noob confusion, but I noticed a couple things:<br />
 * Regarding this image &#8211; <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/images/rel-vs-abs-flex.svg" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/images/rel-vs-abs-flex.svg</a>. Initially I thought this was super helpful. However, when I looked at where it’s used in the w3 spec, it doesn’t actually talk about using “auto” as a value for flex-basis at all (just a value for the &#8220;flex&#8221; shorthand), it just has it in the image for some reason &#8211; <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-property" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-property</a><br />
 * Then I found this section of the spec, and it looks like using “auto” as a value for flex-basis is in debate &#8211; <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-basis-property" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-basis-property</a></p>
<p>Questions:<br />
 * Should we avoid using “flex-basis:auto” for the time being? And if so, should there be a note accompanying that image?<br />
 * Am I right in thinking that the w3 spec is a bit confusing/disorganized in those places? Worthy of me sending a comment/email to somebody?</p>
<p>Lastly: Very, very greatful for this post. Thanks!</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1593464' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1593464", "1593464", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to launchoverit'>Reply</a>          </div>
        </div>

