          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-01-06T14:31:24+00:00">January 6, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Why I gave up as a webdesigner"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Why I gave up as a webdesigner</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Yay, let&#8217;s make CSS even more complicated! W3 crams more and more stuff into HTML and CSS, but forgets that people want to settle and work with it and not study new tags/definitions each day.</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
          <div class="reply">
            <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1598920' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1598920", "1598920", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label='Reply to Why I gave up as a webdesigner'>Reply</a>          </div>
