      <div class="comment-wrap" id="comment-1601197">

        <div class="author-avatar">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" width="50" height="50" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6ff55239f069e204b22596b14e1e63e6?s=160&d=retro&r=pg">
          <svg class="half-circle" width="80px" height="80px">
            <use xlink:href="#half-circle"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-04-27T10:06:36+00:00">April 27, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Chris Simeone"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Chris Simeone</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>This is an awesome post. It has helped me several times.<br />
I am having one issue that I cannot figure out. I can&#8217;t get a single line of text to vertically center within an element. It seems so simple, and yet I&#8217;ve wasted hours without any luck.<br />
Would anyone be willing to comment on this Codepen? Resize the width below 900px and you&#8217;ll see what happens.<br />
<iframe id="cp_embed_mPGQdq" src="https://codepen.io/simspace-dev/embed/preview/mPGQdq?height=300&amp;amp;slug-hash=mPGQdq&amp;amp;default-tabs=css,result&amp;amp;host=http%3A%2F%2Fcodepen.io&amp;amp;embed-version=2" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" height="300" allowtransparency="true" class="cp_embed_iframe" style="width: 100%; overflow: hidden;"></iframe><br />
