        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-08-26T04:42:29+00:00">August 26, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Wouter"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Wouter</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>If you add &#8220;display: flex; align-items: center; height: 100%&#8221; to your .bullet-content class, you should be OK.<br />
The height: 100% is needed to stretch your</p>
<p> element to the li-height (could&#8217;ve done that with flexbox too of course).</p>

          </div>
