            <p>Hi people,</p>
<p>This article has been my &#8220;cheat sheet&#8221; for flex-box standard.<br />
I have encountered a bug on firefox that does not allow  elements to be flex containers.<br />
It took me AGES to find that out, so I wanna share this with other folks that might be going though the pain I have just experienced!</p>
<p>jsbin link that shows bug: <a href="https://jsbin.com/kobefo/1" rel="nofollow">https://jsbin.com/kobefo/1</a><br />
bugzilla link: <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=984869" rel="nofollow">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=984869</a></p>

          </div>
