        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-08-22T05:14:28+00:00">August 22, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Rick"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Rick</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I&#8217;m not clear on whether I would still need prefixing on any flex code as of this writing in August 2016.  If the answer is &#8220;depends on what browser support you need&#8221;, I really wouldn&#8217;t know or couldn&#8217;t predict exactly who might visit my commercial site.</p>
<p>Should prefix code be inserted as a safeguard, OR is it deleterious to add vendor flex prefix code if said vendor has provided full flex compliance in more recent browser versions?</p>
<p>Bottom line: is it just a good idea to add vendor prefixing for flex at this stage of the game and is there any possible downside for doing it now (8/2016)?</p>

          </div>
        </div>
