            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-08-30T08:45:33+00:00">August 30, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Michael"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Michael</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>You can get some useful insights (and ones very specific to your site and users) by installing Google Analytics.  With the statistics it gives you, you can see the browser breakdown of the people who come to your site.  I think that would let you know how much of a need there really is for support for given browser versions.</p>

