        <div class="comment-body">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-time"><time datetime="2016-11-10T03:05:15+00:00">November 10, 2016</time></div> <div class="comment-author"><a href="Andy O."><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> Andy O.</div>
            
          </div>
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I wonder who thought that implementing space-around like that was a good idea and why.</p>
<p>Because I understand equal space between elements as:<br />
A|===|A|===|A|===|A<br />
(&#8220;A&#8221; being a certain distance)</p>
<p>Instead, it is:<br />
A|===|AA|===|AA|===|A</p>
<p>Which makes the laying out of content in an evenly distributed manner impossible.</p>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-actions">
