          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Ola.. I&#8217;m curious about using <code>margin: auto;</code> on children vs the slightly more verbose <code>justify-content: space-around; align-items: center;</code> on the parent. I was playing around with this on Codepen (<a href="https://codepen.io/ZaLiTHkA/pen/VxxZER" rel="nofollow">see this here thing</a>) and I noticed that I could achieve the same layout using either route.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve been bitten by &#8220;100 ways to do X&#8221; from JS too many times, where each one has it&#8217;s own special quirks.. So now I&#8217;m sceptical, which of these two options would be the safest, both for use right now and for other projects going forward?</p>

